I'm willing to do that.

28:01.262 --> 28:06.017
Whatever you think is needed
for the show, that's fine.

28:06.101 --> 28:08.103
NATHAN: Okay, cool.
I'll-- I'll talk to you
in a bit.

28:08.186 --> 28:09.354
ANGELA: Okay. See you.

28:11.564 --> 28:16.736
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

28:25.286 --> 28:27.956
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

28:32.961 --> 28:34.712
(ADAM COUGHING)

28:36.840 --> 28:39.676
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

28:42.387 --> 28:43.430
NATHAN: Adam?

28:44.848 --> 28:46.224
Adam?

28:46.307 --> 28:48.143
-(CLATTERING)
-♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

28:48.226 --> 28:49.811
NATHAN: Adam, Adam, you okay?

28:49.894 --> 28:51.938
-(ADAM RETCHING)
-NATHAN: Are you okay? Breathe.
Breathe. Breathe. Breathe.

28:52.021 --> 28:53.440
Breathe. Breathe. Breathe.
Breathe. Breathe.

28:53.523 --> 28:56.776
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS) ♪

28:56.860 --> 29:00.071
-Angela! Angela!
-ANGELA: What?

29:00.864 --> 29:01.906
NATHAN: Adam, stay with me,

29:01.990 --> 29:04.117
are you okay?
Are you okay, Adam?

29:04.200 --> 29:05.452
-Adam. Adam--
-(COUGHS)

29:05.535 --> 29:06.870
What's going on?

29:06.953 --> 29:09.164
-(ADAM BREATHES HEAVILY)
-NATHAN: Okay, it's all right.

29:09.247 --> 29:10.290
(ADAM RETCHES)

29:10.373 --> 29:11.708
NATHAN: (SOBS) I don't know
what's happening.

29:11.791 --> 29:14.627
I don't know what's happening
to him. I don't know.

29:14.711 --> 29:16.880
I don't know what's happening.

29:16.963 --> 29:19.674
I don't know what's happening
with him.

29:19.757 --> 29:25.180
I don't know.
I don't know. (SOBS)

29:25.263 --> 29:27.307
He's got pinpointed pupils,
hyperventilation.

29:27.390 --> 29:29.893
High end-tidal.
Looks like an opioid overdose.

29:29.976 --> 29:31.394
Okay, with hypertension
we need to consider

29:31.478 --> 29:33.354
-benzo involvement.
-PARAMEDIC 1: Mm-hmm. I agree.

29:33.438 --> 29:34.814
We'll start by assisting
his breathing.

29:34.898 --> 29:36.733
-PARAMEDIC 2: Okay.
-PARAMEDIC 1: Hit him up
with some Narcan.

29:36.816 --> 29:39.819
PARAMEDIC 2: Blood pressure 96
over 50. Respiration, six.

29:39.903 --> 29:41.196
O2 stat, 86.

29:41.279 --> 29:42.530
How are you feeling?
You good?

29:42.614 --> 29:44.073
-You okay?
-(BREATHES HEAVILY)

29:44.157 --> 29:46.493
What are you doing? Don't. No.
Stay, stay. You're safe, Adam.

29:46.576 --> 29:47.994
-You're safe.
-PARAMEDIC 2: Hey, hey, hey!

29:48.077 --> 29:49.412
-Wh-- what's happening?
-NATHAN: Hey!

29:58.838 --> 30:01.049
Have you seen a 15-year-old boy
around here?

30:01.466 --> 30:04.219
PASSERBY:

30:04.302 --> 30:06.554
An older man? No, no.
That wouldn't be him.

30:06.638 --> 30:07.847
Okay, thank you.

30:09.641 --> 30:10.642
Adam?

30:11.559 --> 30:13.895
Oh, sorry. Sorry.

30:16.314 --> 30:20.109
-(BIRDS CHIRPING)
-NATHAN: It's easy to assume

30:20.193 --> 30:22.320
that others think
the worst of you...

30:25.281 --> 30:27.367
but when you assume
what others think,

30:27.450 --> 30:31.162
maybe all you're doing
is turning them into a character

30:31.246 --> 30:33.164
that only exists in your mind.

30:39.963 --> 30:43.132
The nice thing is,
sometimes all it takes

30:43.216 --> 30:45.009
is a change in perspective

30:45.093 --> 30:47.595
to make the world
feel brand-new.

30:52.350 --> 30:54.936
All right, Adam. Let's go home.

31:07.407 --> 31:10.285
(ADAM GRUNTS)

31:18.209 --> 31:19.419
Is that it?

31:19.502 --> 31:23.756
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
